    "summary": "Limble API V2 exposes maintenance-system assets, asset fields and logs, locations, parts with quantities and usage, work-order style tasks, purchase objects, and operational webhooks for assets, tasks, parts, and purchase-order events.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Limble API V2. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. The Limble API V2 docs state that the API covers Assets, Locations, Parts with current quantities and usage, and Tasks including work orders, preventive maintenance, and work requests. The published Postman collection confirms concrete asset, asset-field, asset-log, location, part, and task routes, while the webhook documentation adds change events for assets, parts, and tasks. That makes it a strong asset and maintenance-workflow API with documented writeback, but not a machine-telemetry feed. Asset data is Supported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
